      "side": 1,
      "message": "The new streaming write API has no \"insert IDs\" (at least I could not find them). Instead it has something called offsets, but I don\u0027t think they work with \"_default\" stream. And using non _default stream is a lot more complicated and has various limitations.\n\nSo I don\u0027t think BQ has a way to automatically deduplicate data in case of \"submarine writes\" to \"_default\" stream (when BQ wrote the data, but we failed to receive the ACK and sent it again). Elsewhere they suggest to dedup stuff in queries using UNIQUE() :(",
