      "message": "PTAL (still writing tests, but I manually tested it for real in various edge case conditions).\n\nUsage is very simple:\n\n```\nfunc main() {\n  modules :\u003d []module.Module{\n    bqlog.NewModuleFromFlags(),\n  }\n\n  bqlog.RegisterLoggedType(bqlog.LoggedType{\n    Prototype: \u0026apipb.Logged{},\n    Table:     \"table-id\",\n  })\n\n  server.Main(nil, modules, func(srv *server.Server) error {\n    srv.Routes.GET(\"/\", nil, func(c *router.Context) {\n      bqlog.Log(c.Context, \u0026apipb.Logged{\n        TestInt: time.Now().UnixNano(),\n      })\n    })\n    return nil\n  })\n}\n\n./server -cloud-project some-project -bqlog-dataset some-dataset\n```",
