      "message": "\u003e maybe \"bqlog.Sink\" since this includes the table and also buffering information? (i.e. it\u0027s more than just the type, and IIUC you could have multiple \"LoggedType\"s with the same Prototype and different tables/buffer params)\n\u003e \n\u003e edit: though it looks like Prototype is used as the primary key in bufs... maybe table would be a better key, since you can\u0027t have multiple schemas per table?\n\nUsing the table as a key will require passing it to all Log(...) calls which I don\u0027t like. I don\u0027t think there\u0027s a practical use case of having multiple tables with the same schema. And it wouldn\u0027t be hard to refactor this code if there\u0027s such use case. The only potential issue is using proto message name in metric fields. I guess I\u0027ll replace it with full table ID (project/dataset/table) now.",
